snippet: A two-year study found that vitamin D, which evidence suggested might slow osteoarthritis, neither reduced knee pain nor restored cartilage.
abstract: A two-year study found that vitamin D, which evidence suggested might slow osteoarthritis, neither reduced knee pain nor restored cartilage.

headline.main: Vitamin D Doesn't Reduce Knee Pain
headline.print_headline: Nutrition: Vitamin D Doesn’t Reduce Knee Pain
